Africa is one of the continents and regions used for geographical and cultural identification; 
Life expectancy is a statistical measure of the average time an organism is expected to live, based on the year of its birth, its current age, and other demographic factors including gender; 
Total healthcare expenditure refers to the sum of public and private health expenditures as a percentage of GDP.

Life expectancy is a key indicator of a country's overall health and well-being; 
A lower adult mortality rate generally indicates better healthcare; 
Infant mortality rate is often used as an indicator of a country's healthcare quality; 
HIV/AIDS prevalence is a significant health concern worldwide; 
Total healthcare expenditure can impact a country's ability to provide quality healthcare; 
Vaccination coverage is crucial for preventing the spread of diseases; 
Schooling and literacy rate are important indicators of a country's education system and overall development.
